{[showcards S:ST]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \H4, East plays the \HJ, won by South with \HA.

South plays the \SJ, you follow with \S5, dummy \S3 and East plays the \S2. South continues with the \ST 

Play the \S6.

East's \S2 tells you he had an ODD number of \Ss, obviously 3. Since South also must have 3, you must take your \SA on the third round, depriving dummy of the extra \S trick.

South may now turn to the \D suit, but your side can win the first \D and drive out South's \HK. You will win 2 \Hs, 2 \Ds and the \SA, down 1}
[Play "W"]H4

